div.p:

Thus the firſt conſtitution afforded no certain guarantee either to perſons or things, and the ſecond was found more defective than the firſt. Treaties of peace were quickly broken; 

                  and became the ſource of a new war, ſtill more deſperate and bloody than the former.

               And the directory terrified all Europe; and deſtroyed, according to its caprice, ſeveral governments.
